The paper is about building neural machine translation systems, which falls under the category of natural language processing (NLP). Therefore, cs.CL (Computation and Language) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also mentions the use of attentional encoder-decoder and dropout, which are common techniques in deep learning, suggesting that cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.LG (Machine Learning) are also likely sub-categories. Additionally, the paper mentions the use of back-translations and target-bidirectional models, which are related to neural network architectures, suggesting that cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) is a possible sub-category. Finally, the paper evaluates the performance of the systems using BLEU scores, which is a common metric in information retrieval, suggesting that cs.IR (Information Retrieval) is a possible sub-category as well.
